I’m officially ULTRA Marathoner (50 km). I wanted to end this year with such a high note that next year I have to go way beyond my limits to be better thn this year. 
Honestly it was not at all easy, between 30 to 40 kms I had to convince myself not to give up. Running in Jaisalmer is again a totally different game. 
But I’m loving this version of me who’s pushing to be better everyday.
So I’m telling keep pushing your limits, keep working hard, keep growing, take care of your family and friends. 
Live this life with a smile on your face and never ever give up. ❤️💪🏽
.
.
.

My parents used to take me to Vrindavan since I was one year old, and every year we’d go. I have so many beautiful memories from there. 

On Saturday, we were planning a big bike trip, but then @alicerosario suggested, ‘Why not do a short trip to Vrindavan first?’ I’m glad we did.
Now, there are even more beautiful memories added to my list of Vrindavan experiences.

Life is beautiful. Blessed ❣️✨
